Task: How to position cursor after replaced text, with conditional event handler in rustyline?

 <p>I'm writing a SQL command line tool in Rust, using ODBC to connect to arbitrary SQL databases.  My sqlite test database has the following tables:</p>
<pre class="lang-sql prettyprint-override"><code>CREATE TABLE book (year, authorid, title)
CREATE TABLE author (id, name)
</code></pre>
<p>I'm using the <code>rustyline</code> crate for text entry, and have written some tab completion code to add a space after every unique word completion, so I can continue entering SQL keywords afterwards.  Here the &quot;|&quot; character represents the cursor:</p>
<pre class="lang-sql prettyprint-override"><code>zql&gt; SELECT * FROM bo&lt;TAB&gt;|
zql&gt; SELECT * FROM book |
zql&gt; SELECT * FROM book ORDER BY ti&lt;TAB&gt;|
zql&gt; SELECT * FROM book ORDER BY title |
</code></pre>
<p>In a different context, I want to enter a column name after the table name.  However, if there is already a space after the table, I have to press backspace to delete it before I can enter &quot;.&quot; and the column:</p>
<pre class="lang-sql prettyprint-override"><code>zql&gt; SELECT bo&lt;TAB&gt;|
zql&gt; SELECT book &lt;BKSP&gt;|
zql&gt; SELECT book.title FROM book|
</code></pre>
<p>I would like <code>rustyline</code> to delete any whitespace before the cursor automatically, when I enter &quot;.&quot; or &quot;,&quot;.  So I wrote the following struct:</p>
<pre><code>struct MyEventHandler {
    insert: String,
}

impl MyEventHandler {
    fn new(insert: char) -&gt; MyEventHandler {
        let insert = String::from(insert);
        MyEventHandler { insert }
    }
}

impl ConditionalEventHandler for MyEventHandler {
    fn handle(
        &amp;self,
        _event: &amp;Event,
        _count: RepeatCount,
        _positive: bool,
        context: &amp;EventContext,
    ) -&gt; Option&lt;Cmd&gt; {
        let pos = context.pos();
        let line = context.line();
        let line = &amp;line[0..pos];
        if let Some(index) = line.rfind(|c| !char::is_whitespace(c)) {
            if let Some(count) = pos.checked_sub(index + 1) {
                if count &gt; 0 {
                    let movement = Movement::BackwardChar(count as RepeatCount);
                    return Some(Cmd::Replace(movement, Some(self.insert.clone())));
                }
            }
        }
        None
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>And bound it to keys &quot;.&quot; and &quot;,&quot; using the following function:</p>
<pre><code>fn bind_handler(editor: &amp;mut Editor&lt;CommandHelper, DefaultHistory&gt;, key: char) {
