Task: How to shutdown Tokio BroadcastStream

 <p>I've abstracted a <code>tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender</code> and I am creating new subscribers from a cloned version of it. That subscriber is then fed into a <code>BroadcastStream</code> for SSE. I read that dropping the sender will stop the <code>BroadcastStream</code> (and the SSE). However, I'm cloning it all over the place. How can I &quot;drop&quot; the sender from all these places on an interrupt so that my service can shut down? Below is a sample of the type of abstractions I'm using.</p>
<pre><code>pub fn events_channel() -&gt; (EventSender, EventStreamFactory) {
    let (tx, _) = channel(20);
    (EventSender { tx: tx.clone() }, EventStreamFactory { tx })
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct EventSender {
    tx: Sender&lt;Event&gt;,
}

impl EventSender {
    pub fn send(&amp;self, event: Event) {
        let _ = self.tx.send(event);
    }
}

pub struct EventStreamFactory {
    tx: Sender&lt;Event&gt;,
}

impl EventStreamFactory {
    pub fn all_events(&amp;self) -&gt; impl Stream&lt;Item = Result&lt;Event, RecvError&gt;&gt; + Send + use&lt;&gt; {
        BroadcastStream::new(self.tx.subscribe()).filter_map(|event| match event {
            Ok(event) =&gt; Some(Ok(event)),
            Err(_) =&gt; Some(Err(RecvError)),
        })
    }
}
</code></pre>


