 This happened because we explicitly wrote &'a mut T.

 If we change type Item = (Vec<usize>, &mut T); 
 The compiler will treat this as `&'1 mut T` effectively (where '1 is the borrow of self).
 This is safe because you cannot call next() again while holding the previous reference.
